The Interagency Committee consists of the following members:
The State Superintendent of Schools, or the Superintendent's designee;
A member of the public appointed by the President of the Senate;
A member of the public appointed by the Speaker of the House;
The Secretary of the Department of Planning, or the Secretary's designee; and
The Secretary of General Services, or the Secretary's designee.

A member of the Interagency Committee on School Construction may not be:
An individual who is a regulated lobbyist as described in § 15-701(a)(1), (2), (3), or (4) of the State Government Article;
A member of the General Assembly;
An employee of a county government or board of education; or
A local elected official.
